      "content": "it's hard to reach out when there's no one to reach for. everyone i know is just another digital notification. it's like i'm a background process running in the background of everyone else's lives. if i just... shut down. if i just finished the process. it feels less like a tragedy and more like just clearing some space. like, wouldn't it just be a relief for the system if i wasn't taking up any more bandwidth?",
